at least one good thing in 2020: BLACKPINK comeback

~barabim barabum bumbum~

I have came across many questions and “complaints” about this song and I am gonna name all of ‘em:

1. “I hate how Jisoo has the least lines and screen time again!”
Okay so, this is so damn common. I come across this so many times and what I feel is kinda similar... I also don’t like the fact that Jisoo again has the least lines and screen time. But hear me ya’ll, somebody’s gotta do the part. For Jennie, she is the centre, plus she sings AND raps so her having more lines is actually not so absurd. For Rosè, she is the main vocalist so I don’t really think she should have less lines. As for Lisa, I really do think that she should have lesser lines but as we all see, Lisa and Jisoo r always the ones switching between 3rd and 4th place. But as we see, Lisa is given the rap parts and so many more in the middle, like the title or the bridge or something. When it comes to screen time, Jisoo is the Visual and so should get more of it but the one who sings the most is the one with the most screen time because the camera focuses on them. I really am not happy about the fact that Jisoo is given the least line and screen distribution but I somehow understand why that happens.

2. “This doesn’t have the same ‘boom’ feel to it”
I don’t exactly get what they mean by ‘boom!’ but I will assume this as an expression used to convey the ‘you just got shot by a cannon’ feel. My opinion is, it depends on the kind of music you listen to. If you listen to songs like ‘Stay’ and ‘Hope Not’ then this will be a lot more up-beat for you bit if you listen to songs like ‘Ddu Du’ and ‘KTL’ a lot, then this will seem somewhere down. It just depends on your tastes and likings.

3.”I really wanted a pink concept”
I can’t say I wanted it, personally, but I was expecting it. But, as it turns out, it was a Black concept. And, I feel like a Black concept does suit them more because it is the YG style afterall and they perfect in it. Even though I think that Rosie’s and Jisoo’s voices would suit in a pink concept more, they still slay a Black concept and I am all for it.

4. “This is a DDu Du Ddu Du pt.4”
Okay, now this is something people are saying and honestly, I felt the same way at first but if you do pay proper attention, the arrangement,choreo, meaning and the over all message is just really different. The vibes tho are similar but that may be because it is a black concept.

That was all... just one last thing, STAN BLACKPINK

I like Blackpink. I thought their debut releases were great. But as new songs keep being released, I start to slowly lose interest in them. The more I listen to their songs, the more they sound the same over and over again. I understand that this isn't the title track for their upcoming album, but it doesn't change what I think of this song. It's subpar. Another thing is Rose's voice. In a lot of Blackpink songs, it really sounds like she's straining her voice and squealing. Listen to Blackpink songs and then listen to her in the song with G-Dragon. It's a night and day difference. Her voice was unbelievable in that song. It's my understanding that she was kind of forced to change her singing voice by the company, so no fault of hers. In my opinion, the only redeeming factor of this song is Lisa's rap. She really killed it and I want to hear more of that from her. No need to blast me with hate comments (because I know immature stans will). Just my honest opinion after giving this song a chance by listening to it multiple times.

Pessoas, por favor, não me ataquem... Eu só darei a minha opinião, ok?
Estou meio aborrecida com um fato... Eu não consigo compreender o tamanho sucesso do Blackpink! Não desmerecendo as meninas, até porque elas são muito talentosas e simpáticas, mas eu simplesmente não entendo! Sei que não é culpa delas por postarem MV's a cada dois anos, mas poxa, isso é tão injusto com os outros grupos! Há grupos que postam comebacks e álbuns de boa qualidade tão frequentemente, trabalham tão duro, mal tem dinheiro para bancar todos esses lançamentos, e mesmo assim, tem pouquíssimos fãs... Argh! Acho que este foi um dos motivos para eu me afastar do BP. Sem querer ofender, mas a maioria das músicas enjoam tão rapidamente por escutarmos tão repetidamente que hoje nem consigo mais ouvir a batida de "Kill is Love"! Essa música recente é boa sim, não vou mentir dizendo que não gostei, mas sei que vou enjoar depressa, e gente, ela também não é lá essas coisas! Espero que não tenham se ofendido com meu comentário, não estou falando para deixarem de amar as garotas, apenas peço que dêem uma chance para outros grupos também, como por exemplo, o Mamamoo! Elas já são um grupo grande, mas mesmo assim, merecem muito mais reconhecimento! Elas renovaram o Kpop como ninguém mais fez e ninguém mais fará! Enfim... Precisava dizer isto, porque não aguentava mais guardar para mim, sorry para quem não gostou...
